description.narrative:
In the preparation phase (3 months):
- Recruit project team;
- A start-up meeting will be held with the participation of all stakeholders involved, including: Plan regional office of the Americas, Plan Brazil, Plan Holland, Cryuff Foundation and WomenWin;
- The La League – Champions of Change methodology is developed, and trainers are trained;
- La League project team is trained in the LEEP methodology and Heroes methodology;
- A baseline study will be conducted regarding the incidence of teenage pregnancy and child marriage in the selected communities;
- 01 market study if developed and conducted by external consultant;

In the implementation phase (30 month):
- 525 Both boys and girl’s champions of change workshop sessions are held;
- Weekly football training with the 350 girls that are Champions of Change;
- Groups of boys/girls, led by girls and supported by father’s design and carry out community events to raise awareness about the harmful practices of child marriage and teenage pregnancy and other project thematic among their peers and in their communities, reaching other 750 peer boys and girls;
-750 community members are engaged and committed to improve gender equality in their daily lives;
- La League project team is trained in Heroes methodology;
- 50 girls are selected and trained in economic empowerment LEEP methodology and have access to sports related opportunities (courses, jobs, internships, informal initiatives, technical trainings);
- Engaging 175 fathers, brothers and other male figures through girl’s football activities;
- 35 number father/daughter events have been organised;
- 02 La League tournaments at local level are organized;
- 01 Public campaign is held on the impact of girl’s football and gender equality in Brazil;
- 09 Football pitches are made fit for use in each community and teams are set up;
- 01 official Cryuff court is built and maintained in one central community in the Codó region.
